    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section id="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>How does the bucket list generator work?</summary>
        <div class="answer">Select one or more categories, set optional filters for cost range, difficulty, and solo vs group — then click Generate. The tool pulls matching ideas from a curated database of 150+ real experiences and displays them with estimated costs, difficulty ratings, and descriptions.</div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Is my bucket list saved?</summary>
        <div class="answer">Yes. Your bucket list is stored in your browser's localStorage, so it persists between visits on the same device and browser. No account or sign-up is required. You can also export your list as plain text to save or share it.</div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can I add my own custom bucket list ideas?</summary>
        <div class="answer">Absolutely. In the My Bucket List tab, expand the "Add Custom Idea" form and enter any goal you like — with a title, category, and optional notes. Custom ideas are tracked alongside generator ideas.</div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What do the difficulty levels mean?</summary>
        <div class="answer"><strong>Easy</strong> — minimal planning or cost; you could do it this weekend. <strong>Medium</strong> — requires some preparation, travel, or moderate expense. <strong>Hard</strong> — significant planning, training, or budget. <strong>Epic</strong> — a once-in-a-lifetime challenge that may take months or years of preparation.</div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How were these bucket list ideas chosen?</summary>
        <div class="answer">The ideas are curated from popular travel blogs, adventure communities, and life-experience surveys. They range from free local activities to multi-thousand-dollar adventures, so there is something achievable for every budget and lifestyle.</div>
      </details>
    </section>
